Photo taken during the Blizzard  on January 23rd 2016 …..
.
Right before I took that photo I was threatened to have my camera gear stolen or worst….
.
A large man asked me for a dollar as I walked by him, I didn’t respond, then he said how about that camera around your neck…He proceeded to inform me that there were no cops around as he continued to follow me …I had my tripod compacted in my hand and I was preparing to swing away in case he attacked ….
.
Luckily he stopped following me …
.
So what’s my point, to all of the people that want to venture out in a storm, first see if you can go out with a few friends, you’ll have more fun, you’ll get better photos and you’ll be safer…
.

I had the honor of photographing the sunset from the deck of the Intrepid Air, Sea and Space Museum tonight @intrepidmuseum ….

My imagination ran wild up there as I was the only one up there on the carrier deck…I think I could almost hear whispers of some of the 55,000 men that served their country on this ship …
.
I was here to check out what they had going on for Kids Week, which is till next Sat…
.
I took a friend with her Kids tonight… Honestly the kids were a little nervous about going aboard the intrepid… But once they reached the kids section and saw all of the activities the intrepid had in store for them, they had the time of their lives…I’ll be sharing more about it tomorrow ….
.
Happy Sunday 😬

A photograph from the snow storm that wasn’t meant to be from last night …
.
Not the best photo I’ve taken but it will have to do for now ….
.
(Warning I am about to go on a rant)
If I take a video clip I have to take a photo… 
.
I feel like so many people are complaining they don’t see photos anymore on instagram… I don’t think it’s all Instagram’s fault either as I think many photographers have almost abandoned photography completely for video.
.
Many accounts I used to love looking at for their photos are now only producing videos mainly …
.
When I first started photography I was inspired by other peoples photography, it was a mystery how they created and sculpted that image … And even though there was no music attached to the photo, a powerful image rang loud in my head …
.
I actually believe it is much harder to take a good photograph over a video, as you only have one frame to share a mood and tell a story… 
.
I also think that people who start off with studying photography have an advantage over film makers who never did photography…
.
So what is my rant about tonight :)? I don’t know, I’m just trying to remind people not to forget about photography, and if we want to see more photos then we have to share more photos …
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

“Mount Manhattan” …,,,One of the most dangerous and rewarding climbs in the world…
.
Many people come here every day with bags packed full of dreams and aspirations and many of the same people leave this city every day with empty bags that were once filled with hope ….
.
Some of you who are actually reading this may be thinking, wow this just got dark fast :) and where is he going with this …I’m wondering that to right now, lol…
.
Well…
.
To succeed in this town, you need mental endurance, you don’t just need to have a plan, you need to be in mental shape … The city is a mental ladder of success … 
.
Quite often I try to accomplish something here and fail or get rejected… It would be easy to say I quit, I had enough, the pain of failing is immense… But I learned the secret to have success or some level of success in this city…Is that my many failures add up to zero, But the few Yes’s I get add up to a huge sum… A sum of success that compounds over time …
.
How successful you are in this town is totally up to you, how much are you willing to stomach to get to that elusive Yes you are seeking … They add up quickly overtime ….
.
So to the people who are having a hard time here, my message is to keep trying, the elusive Yes you are seeking is just around the block …And when you get a Yes don’t to forget to celebrate it!
.
Happy Thursday 🙌

This year I am going to be doing something different on my Fall getaway trip…
.
Instead of staying in hotels I will be traveling in a Van/RV with @vanishtravelco  and parking at campsites…
.
Some of you may be asking why I would do this as oppose to a hotel or Air BNB…
.
For one most hotels are sold out during peak foliage season a year in advance … And I particularly don’t want to book that early because I can only take off 3 or 4 days and if I go on a trip I want to see and experience fall at its peak….it’s hard to know that far in advance which days will be the peak…
.
In the past my friends and I have ended up booking hotels really far away from where we plan on visiting … The two times of the day we focus on are sunrise and sunset …. Driving hours to each location only to later back track hours to our far away hotel … Honestly in prior trips I only get about 3 hours of sleep if I’m lucky… When I get home I’m wrecked  from lack of sleep … Always worth it though …but I would like less driving and more sleep..
.
But this time by using a Nimble RV I will be able to save time by being able to stay nearby each location I plan on visiting … Which will allow to have more time to enjoy each moment and to get enough sleep a human requires to function properly :)
.
I am excited for this trip, and I’ll be sharing as much as I can here …
